data_store_id.description: The unique id of the data store.

exact_match.description: If set to false, a uri_pattern is generated to include all pages whose address contains the provided_uri_pattern. If set to true, an uri_pattern is generated to try to be an exact match of the provided_uri_pattern or just the specific page if the provided_uri_pattern is a specific one. provided_uri_pattern is always normalized to generate the URI pattern to be used by the search engine.

generated_uri_pattern.description: This is system-generated based on the 'provided_uri_pattern'.

location.description: The geographic location where the data store should reside. The value can only be one of "global", "us" and "eu".

name.description: The unique full resource name of the target site. Values are of the format 'projects/{project}/locations/{location}/collections/{collection_id}/dataStores/{data_store_id}/siteSearchEngine/targetSites/{target_site_id}'. This field must be a UTF-8 encoded string with a length limit of 1024 characters.

provided_uri_pattern.description: The user provided URI pattern from which the 'generated_uri_pattern' is generated.

site_verification_info.description: Site ownership and validity verification status.

target_site_id.description: The unique id of the target site.

type.description: The possible target site types. Possible values: ["INCLUDE", "EXCLUDE"]

update_time.description: The target site's last updated time.
